    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-19T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-19T09:00:00-05:00" n="356"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d356">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711F.1914/293: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-19T09:00:00-05:00"
                            >June 19, 1941—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:03 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>145. Last night’s Government paper published a statement by President Arias,
                    commenting pessimistically on the negotiations in Washington and expressing the
                    hope that President Roosevelt would “intervene” in order that they might result
                    successfully. Text by subsequent telegram.<note n="35" xml:id="d356fn35"
                        >Telegram No. 146, June 19, 10 a.m., not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>From conversations with members of the Cabinet, it would seem that de Roux has
                    reported that the attitude of President Roosevelt is all that could be desired,
                    but that resistance is being encountered at the State Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
